          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
Below is the pinout of Audio Input 2 (NF2), when looking
into the <a href="../../../ref/conn/din/index.htm#din_45322"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: 6-pin 240&#176; DIN socket">6-pin 240&#176; DIN socket</span></a>.
This in&#173;put is mutually exclusive with the <b>ZF2</b> intermediate frequency input.
The desired input is selected &mdash; along with the baudrate &mdash; with
<a href="#conf_s1"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Jump to: selector ...">selector <b>S1</b></span></a> at the top of the device.
