Below is the wiring of the cable that is used to connect
the <span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Audio Frequency">AF</span> output of the DE-1710 de&#173;mo&#173;du&#173;la&#173;tor of the
<a href="../../../df/telefunken/e1800"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: Telefunken E-1800 receiver">Telefunken E-1800 receiver</span></a>
to the <span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Audio Frequency">AF</span>-input (NF1) of the Hagenuk TG-1001M.
Note that both devices have the same
<a href="../../../ref/conn/din/index.htm#din_45322"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: 5-pin 240&#176; DIN connector">5-pin 240&#176; DIN connector</span></a>,
but with a <u>different pinout</u>.
