<a href="#conn_fax"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Jump to: FAX-VIDEO output">FAX-VIDEO output</span></a> of the TG-1001M (6-pin DIN 240&#176;) to the
<a href="../../../telex/rs/ga082/index.htm#conn_demod"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: FSK input (BNC)">FSK input (BNC)</span></a>
of the <a href="../../../telex/rs/ga082"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: GA-082">GA-082</span></a>. Note that this is a
single-ended (unbalanced) output with a level of &#177;6V (MIL-188) or
&#177;12V (RS232). It is best to <a href="#conf_v24"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Jump to: configure the device for RS232">configure the device for RS232</span></a>
(&#177;12V).
