          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+0" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          Select mains voltage
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
          <table 
           border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" ><tr><td align="center" valign=top>
            <div style="position: relative;">
            <div style="position: relative;">
            <img src="../../../img/blank.gif"
             style="
             max-width: 618px;
            "
             align="left"
             vspace="4"
             border=0
             width=1 height=1
             />
            <img src="../../../stamp/danger.svg" style="position: absolute; top: 15px; left: 630px;" 
            />
            </div>
            </td></tr><tr><td align=center>
          </td></tr></table>
The device is suitable for connection to the 115V <u>or</u> 230V <span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Alternating Current">AC</span> mains,
selectable with a <a href="img/304293/023/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: slide switch inside the device">slide switch inside the device</span></a>.
Ensure that the appropriate voltage is selected <b>before</b> connecting the
device to the mains. Also note that mains voltages are potentially lethal.
Always disconnect the device from the mains before opening it. Open the
device <b>only</b> if you know exactly what you are doing.
<br />
<br /><font color="#E7E">&#10148;</font>&nbsp;<a href="img/304293/023/full.jpg">115/230V selector</a>
<br />
<br />
          </font>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
<br />        <a name=conf_s1></a>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
          <tr>
          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+0" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          Input selection and baud rate 
          &nbsp;<font color="#CCC">
          S1
          </font>
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
The desired input (<span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Audio Frequency">AF</span> or <span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Intermedia Frequency">IF</span>) and baudrate, are selected with a
<a href="img/304293/020/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: 16-position rotary switch">16-position rotary switch</span></a> that is accessible
through a <a href="img/304293/013/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: hole (marked S1) in the top panel">hole (marked S1) in the top panel</span></a>
of the device. Use a screwdriver to set the switch to the desired position
(0-9 and A-F), according to the table below.
          </font>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
